{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-608-Whats-New-in-GameplayKit"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16"]]},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (41 min)","type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc16\/608"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"GameplayKit provides developers a collection of essential tools and techniques used to implement modern gameplay algorithms. Learn what’s new in GameplayKit and check out advances in pathfinding, autonomous agents, and game AI, as well as many enhancements supporting GameplayKit in Xcode. Tap into new capabilities for 2D and 3D spatial partitioning, and explore noise-based procedural data generation useful for height maps, natural textures, and more."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-608-whats-new-in-gameplaykit"]}],"metadata":{"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC16","title":"What’s New in GameplayKit","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Updates in:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Pathfinding","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Agents"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"GameAI (formerly known as MinMax AI)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Three new features:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spatial partitioning","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Procedural generation","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Xcode integration (with the Xcode editor, not only in code!)","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"PathFinding","level":2,"anchor":"PathFinding"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKMeshGraph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Instead of computing line of sight possible paths (like with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKObstacleGraph","type":"reference"},{"text":"), ","type":"text"},{"code":"GKMeshGraph","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" uses triangle mesh, where every possible point in the map is represented in one and only one triangle.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Less memory intensive, faster to compute, good results (not best tho!)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Node location flexibility: triangle center, vertices, edges (it can be any of them, even combination of them). The more elements, the more compute intensive","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC16-608-PathFinding","type":"image"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"￼","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Agents","level":2,"anchor":"Agents"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3D support ("},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKAgent3D","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and associated classes)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"New Behavior composition (similar to weighted goals)","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Spatial Partitioning","level":2,"anchor":"Spatial-Partitioning"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Does a spacial caching of the map to answer quicker to inquiries such as:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"How many enemies are near the player?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Where are all items in the my world?"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Which projectiles will hit player this frame?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The way it works is by creating a tree out of the map, the more elements, the more the nodes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Three possible trees:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"R-trees","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"quadtree"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"octrees","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"R-tree is a tree data structure that has a number of hierarchical buckets:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"whenever you add an object to an R-tree, it gets fitted into one of those buckets.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"when these buckets grow too large, they need to split: this is a user-configurable parameter of just how large these buckets can grow"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"we have a number of strategies at our disposal to decide how these buckets should split","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"all R-trees do is putting things in buckets","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC16-608-rtree"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Quadtree and octrees solve the same problem, quad tree on 2D, octrees in 3D:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"these are tree-like data structures that have a number of levels and hierarchies","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"space is subdivided evenly at each level"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"have a max cell size associated, this controls just how deep these trees can grow and just how small those cells can get.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"when you add an object to a quadtree or octree, it gets placed into the smallest cell that it fits in entirely","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC16-608-rtree-2","type":"image"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When we create a tree, we need to define the minimum size cell: e.g. no cell in this quadtree is going to be smaller than that.","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"We’re setting an hard limit on how small (and how many levels deep) our tree can go.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Game AI","level":2,"anchor":"Game-AI"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Last year GameplayKit introduced the MinMax Strategist, this year we’re adding Monte Carlo strategist."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This new strategist doesn’t guarantee the best outcome (unlike minMax), but it’s much faster."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This year also we can create our own strategist via "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKStrategist","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"New ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKDecisionTree","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":": these are a trees that can be handmade or make the AI learn, and are useful when we have many states and the AI needs to make decisions fast.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Procedural generation","level":2,"anchor":"Procedural-generation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is to create new worlds\/textures\/.. and dynamic things like that, good for games that are not static and need to continuously create new things\/levels.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"What procedural generation does is help us with some coherent randomness.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Plenty of different noises available, noises can be combined together.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Xcode integration","level":2,"anchor":"Xcode-integration"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Previously everything was done via code, now we can use editors like we do for CoreData and SpriteKit:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Entity and Components Editor"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Navigation Graph Editor"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Scene Outline View"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"State Machine Quick Look (directly from the debugger!)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"We can use the new callout ","type":"text"},{"code":"@GKInspectable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in our components properties to make them show up in the editor","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Written By","level":2,"anchor":"Written-By"},{"type":"row","numberOfColumns":5,"columns":[{"size":1,"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"zntfdr"}]}]},{"size":4,"content":[{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"zntfdr","anchor":"zntfdr"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Contributed Notes","type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contributed Notes"}]},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"|"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/"}]}]}]},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Missing anything? Corrections? ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference"}]},{"type":"heading","text":"Related Sessions","level":2,"anchor":"Related-Sessions"},{"type":"links","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-601-Go-Live-with-ReplayKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-609-Advances-in-SceneKit-Rendering","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-610-Whats-New-in-SpriteKit","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-611-Whats-New-in-Game-Center","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-612-Game-Technologies-for-Apple-Watch"],"style":"list"},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Legal Notice","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"}]},{"type":"small","inlineContent":[{"text":"All content copyright © 2012 – 2025 Apple Inc. All rights reserved.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Swift, the Swift logo, Swift Playgrounds, Xcode, Instruments, Cocoa Touch, Touch ID, FaceID, iPhone, iPad, Safari, Apple Vision, Apple Watch, App Store, iPadOS, watchOS, visionOS, tvOS, Mac, and macOS are trademarks of Apple Inc., registered in the U.S. and other countries.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This website is not made by, affiliated with, nor endorsed by Apple.","type":"text"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"article","references":{"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-612-Game-Technologies-for-Apple-Watch":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-612-Game-Technologies-for-Apple-Watch","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-612-game-technologies-for-apple-watch","title":"Game Technologies for Apple Watch","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"watchOS 3 adds a lineup of technologies for developing games that are responsive, lightweight, and fun. Gain insights into techniques for creating great games for Apple Watch. Discover how to take advantage of gesture recognizers and the Digital Crown for gameplay, SpriteKit and SceneKit for 2D and 3D graphics, and Game Center for turn-based multiplayer games.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"zntfdr":{"identifier":"zntfdr","alt":"Profile image of zntfdr","type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/gameplaykit/GKAgent3D":{"title":"GKAgent3D","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GKAgent3D"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKAgent3D","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKAgent3D"},"https://":{"url":"https:\/\/","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Blog","type":"text"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/","title":"Blog"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/gameplaykit/GKObstacleGraph":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKObstacleGraph","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKObstacleGraph","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"GKObstacleGraph","type":"codeVoice"}],"title":"GKObstacleGraph"},"WWDC16-608-PathFinding":{"identifier":"WWDC16-608-PathFinding","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-608-PathFinding.png"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16":{"abstract":[{"text":"Xcode 8, Swift 3.0, iOS 10, macOS 10.12 (Sierra), tvOS 10, watchOS 3.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16","title":"WWDC16","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16"},"https://developer.apple.com/wwdc16/608":{"checksum":null,"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc16\/608","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/wwdc16\/608"},"WWDC16.jpeg":{"identifier":"WWDC16.jpeg","alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16.jpeg"}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/gameplaykit/GKStrategist":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKStrategist","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"GKStrategist","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKStrategist","title":"GKStrategist"},"WWDC16-608-rtree-2":{"identifier":"WWDC16-608-rtree-2","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-608-rtree-2.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/gameplaykit/GKDecisionTree":{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKDecisionTree","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKDecisionTree","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GKDecisionTree"}],"title":"GKDecisionTree"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","kind":"symbol","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes"},"WWDC16-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC16-Icon.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"zntfdr.jpeg":{"identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg","type":"image","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"WWDC16-608-rtree":{"identifier":"WWDC16-608-rtree","alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-608-rtree.png"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-610-Whats-New-in-SpriteKit":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-610-Whats-New-in-SpriteKit","kind":"article","title":"What’s New in SpriteKit","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-610-whats-new-in-spritekit","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"SpriteKit adds new features to make it even easier to create high-performance, power-efficient 2D games. See how tile maps enable you to lay out large scenes quickly and check out new APIs for warp transformations and custom shader attributes. Learn about focus-based interactions on Apple TV, rendering on Apple Watch, and new tools built right into Xcode for measuring performance and integrating with GameplayKit.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"https://developer.apple.com/documentation/gameplaykit/GKMeshGraph":{"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKMeshGraph","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"GKMeshGraph","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/gameplaykit\/GKMeshGraph","title":"GKMeshGraph"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/zntfdr":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/zntfdr","type":"topic","images":[{"type":"card","identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg"},{"type":"icon","identifier":"zntfdr.jpeg"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/zntfdr","title":"zntfdr (332 notes)","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"No Bio on GitHub","type":"text"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-611-Whats-New-in-Game-Center":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-611-Whats-New-in-Game-Center","kind":"article","title":"What’s New in Game Center","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-611-whats-new-in-game-center","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"Dive into the latest additions to Game Center, Apple’s social gaming network. Check out new capabilities for persistent game sessions and how they provide added flexibility for single-player, real-time multiplayer, and turn-based games. Learn about changes that streamline Game Center and a new way to send game invites and join multiplayer matches.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-609-Advances-in-SceneKit-Rendering":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-609-advances-in-scenekit-rendering","kind":"article","type":"topic","role":"sampleCode","title":"Advances in SceneKit Rendering","abstract":[{"text":"SceneKit is a fully featured high-level graphics framework enabling your apps and games to create 3D animated scenes and effects. Witness the biggest leap forward in SceneKit yet with the introduction of its new Physically-Based Renderer (PBR). Dive into new APIs for accurate materials, physically-based lights, HDR effects, and enhancements in Model I\/O. Walk through an example game using PBR and see how to integrate its workflow into your development.","type":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-609-Advances-in-SceneKit-Rendering"},"https://github.com/zntfdr":{"title":"GitHub","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"GitHub","type":"text"}],"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr","type":"link","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/zntfdr"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC16-601-Go-Live-with-ReplayKit":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC16-601-Go-Live-with-ReplayKit","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc16-601-go-live-with-replaykit","title":"Go Live with ReplayKit","role":"sampleCode","abstract":[{"text":"ReplayKit is an easy-to-use framework that enables players to share gameplay recordings or broadcast live games to players and viewers online. Watch how live broadcasting can help build community and create new fans for your apps and games. Understand the APIs to include player commentary via the microphone and front-facing camera on iPhone and iPad, and check out new support for ReplayKit on Apple TV.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"Contributions are welcome!","type":"text"}],"title":"Contributions are welcome!"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]}}}